# pyenv
#   For a library or package, you might want to ignore these files since the Python version
#   is customized by the app using the library; however, to produce reproducible environments
#   manually maintain .python-version if you'd like.
# .python-version

# pipenv
#   According to pypa/pipenv#1173, pipenv should attach to its own .venv if it exists.
#   However, it's recommended to NOT include .venv in version control.
#   Feel free to uncomment these lines if you work with pipenv.
#   export PIPENV_VENV_IN_PROJECT=1
#   .venv

# poetry
#   Similar to pipenv, poetry should attach to its own virtualenv.
#   You can configure poetry to create virtualenv inside the project structure.
#   .venv
#   poetry.lock

# pdm
#   Similar to pipenv, pdm should attach to its own virtualenv.
#   .pdm-python
#   .pdm-build/

# PEP 582; used by e.g. github.com/fannheyward/coc-pyright
__pypackages__/

